<subSubSection id="C33C618C710B504FFF1CF9F045679F0F" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B993207710B504FFF1CF9F045679F0F" blockId="9.[151,1436,1663,2010]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,152,978]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B952EE15710B504CFF1CF9F046409B8C" bold="true" box="[151,296,1663,1689]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description</emphasis>
. Maximum length ca. 6.0–7.0 mm, elongate-ovoid, subcylindrical; head with frontovertex broad, slightly produced between eyes; eyes large, inner margins diverging dorsally; circumocular groove along inner margin extending more than half of eye circumference; supra-antennal groove above large antennal cavities; antennal cavities narrowly separated; clypeal margin broadly emarginate; gena with shallow transverse depression for basal antennomeres in repose; distal margin of gena with stout, acute tooth; antennae serrate from antennomere 4; pronotum wider than long, wider near midpoint, narrowing to posterior margin; anterior margin convex medially; posterior margin sinuate on either side of bispinose prescutellar lobe; disc transversely convex, except for slight depression on either side of middle in posterior 1/2; lateral margin crenulate; one premarginal carina on either side; scutellum biplanar, wider than long; elytra slightly narrower than maxi- mum pronotal width, widest across humeri and at about posterior 1/3; humeri moderately elevated; lateral margin biarcuate, narrowing medially, apices separately rounded, lateroapical margin finely serrate; disc transversely convex; epipleuron not extending to apex, widest in anterior 1/3, with margin subparallel to elytral margin; pygidium not visible beyond elytra, with apical margin entire; prosternum short, longitudinally compressed, with short, feebly, steeply declivous, bilobed mentonniere; disc transversely convex; process broad, subparallel between procoxae, apex feebly trilobed; abdominal ventrites feebly expanded laterally, ventrites 1 and 2 longer than 3+4+5; ventrite 5 with premarginal groove, apex entire, without sexual morphology; legs with tibiae subquadrate in cross-section, feebly arcuate outer edge; tarsi with tarsomeres 1–4 with ventral pulvilli; tarsal claws bifid. Male genitalia with parameres fully sclerotized; female genitalia with ovipositor of tubular configuration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C618C7108504FFF4DFDA846309F7F" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9932077108504FFF4DFDA846309F7F" blockId="10.[151,1436,152,978]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFF4DFDA846239F54" bold="true" box="[198,331,551,577]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology</emphasis>
. The masculine genus-group name combines the root from the country name with the suffix from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2649847108504FFF5CFDDF46399F7C" authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[215,337,592,617]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Meliboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFF5CFDDF46399F7C" box="[215,337,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Meliboeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C618C7108504FFF4DFDF844459EC7" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9932077108504FFF4DFDF844459EC7" blockId="10.[151,1436,152,978]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFF4DFDF846259F84" bold="true" box="[198,333,631,657]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Comments</emphasis>
. The definition of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2649847108504FFDDEFDF744EE9F87" authority="Deyrolle, 1864" authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[597,902,632,658]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Meliboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFDDEFDF745A79F84" box="[597,719,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Meliboeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFD5DFDF744EE9F87" author="Deyrolle, H." box="[726,902,632,658]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 280" refId="ref8273" refString="Deyrolle, H. (1864) Description des Buprestides de la Malaisie recueilles par M. Wallace pendant son voyage dans cet Archipel. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique, 8, 1 - 280, 4 plates, i - iii in color. [English summary including keys in Zoological Record for 1865]" type="book chapter" year="1864">Deyrolle, 1864</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
genus-group constituency is currently in flux (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFF14FD2F46219FAF" author="Bellamy, C. L." box="[159,329,672,698]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="315 - 324" refId="ref7608" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (1990) The Meliboeus Deyrolle generic group, and further nomenclatural chantges, in the Afrotropical Coroebini Bedel (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Agrilinae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 43 (4) (1989), 315 - 324." type="journal article" year="1990">Bellamy 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFEDDFD2F46C89FAF" author="Bellamy, C. L." box="[342,416,672,698]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="145 - 158" refId="ref7871" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (2006 a) Nomenclatural notes and corrections in Buprestidae (Coleoptera). The Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 81 (3 / 4), 145 - 158." type="journal article" year="2006">2006a</bibRefCitation>
, Kubáň 2006). This new monotypic genus is proposed now for the 
<typeStatus id="549D8CA57108504FFB36FD2F43879FAF" box="[1213,1263,672,698]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species which lacks several of the important character states that define 
<taxonomicName id="4C2649847108504FFCCEFD4743149FF7" authority="Deyrolle, 1864" authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[837,1148,712,738]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Meliboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFCCEFD4744D79FF4" box="[837,959,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Meliboeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFC43FD4743149FF7" author="Deyrolle, H." box="[968,1148,712,738]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 280" refId="ref8273" refString="Deyrolle, H. (1864) Description des Buprestides de la Malaisie recueilles par M. Wallace pendant son voyage dans cet Archipel. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique, 8, 1 - 280, 4 plates, i - iii in color. [English summary including keys in Zoological Record for 1865]" type="book chapter" year="1864">Deyrolle, 1864</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, most notably the entire transverse carina of the hypomeron, the irregularly spinose margin of the pygidium and the membranous lateral projections of the parameres (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFDD9FC9745939E27" author="Bellamy, C. L." box="[594,763,792,818]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="315 - 324" refId="ref7608" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (1990) The Meliboeus Deyrolle generic group, and further nomenclatural chantges, in the Afrotropical Coroebini Bedel (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Agrilinae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 43 (4) (1989), 315 - 324." type="journal article" year="1990">Bellamy 1990</bibRefCitation>
). This new genus-group taxon is placed within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2649847108504FFAC5FC9746459E4F" authorityName="Majer" authorityYear="2001" pageId="10" pageNumber="10" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Amorphosomatina">Amorphosomatina</taxonomicName>
and keys to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2649847108504FFD83FCCF44199E4F" authority="Bellamy, 1988" authorityName="Bellamy" authorityYear="1988" box="[520,881,832,858]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Cryptomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFD83FCCF45DC9E4C" box="[520,692,832,857]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Cryptomorpha</emphasis>
Bellamy, 1988
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2649847108504FFC0CFCCF438C9E4F" authority="Obenberger, 1923" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1923" box="[903,1252,832,858]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Vanroonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFC0CFCCF43689E4C" box="[903,1024,832,857]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Vanroonia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFB86FCCF438C9E4F" author="Obenberger, J." box="[1037,1252,832,858]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="13 - 44" refId="ref8722" refString="Obenberger, J. (1923) R ada novych rod u c eledi Buprestidae (Coleoptera). Une serie de nouveaux genres de Buprestides. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 1, 13 - 44." type="journal article" year="1923">Obenberger, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
couplet in the generic key I published earlier (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFDAEFCE7458C9E97" author="Bellamy, C. L." box="[549,740,872,898]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="101 - 114" refId="ref7485" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (1988 a) Studies in the African Agrilinae, Coroebini VI (Coleoptera, Buprestidae). Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 51 (1), 101 - 114." type="journal article" year="1988">Bellamy 1988a</bibRefCitation>
). Considering the large number of species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2649847108504FFAA9FCE742F49E94" authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[1314,1436,872,897]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Meliboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFAA9FCE742F49E94" box="[1314,1436,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Meliboeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from Subsaharan Africa (113 spp., 
<emphasis id="B952EE157108504FFD38FC1F45B79EBC" box="[691,735,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">fide</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74FF67108504FFD63FC1F44F09EBF" author="Bellamy, C. L." box="[744,920,912,938]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref7657" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (1991) A catalogue of the Coroebini of sub-Saharan Africa (Coleoptera: Buprestidae). Department of Agriculture and Water Supply, Republic of South Africa, Entomology Memoirs, No. 81, 19 pp." type="book" year="1991">Bellamy, 1991</bibRefCitation>
), it will not be surprising to find additional species that should be transferred to this or other genera.
</paragraph>
